HEADWORD: Grievancer
<hw>Griev"an*cer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who occasions
a grievance; one who gives ground for complaint.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Petition . . . against the bishops as grand
<qex>grievancers</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj></p>

